BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Central Bank Survey, Currency Measures Talks

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-04-04T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/brazil-daybook-central-bank-survey-currency-measures-talks.html
The central bank releases today a
weekly survey of about 100 economists on expectations for the
country’s inflation, growth and  interest rates . Estimates for
2011 consumer prices rose in the three past surveys.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega will discuss possible measures
to stem the currency’s appreciation, a government official said.  ECONOMY:
*FIPE monthly CPI index at 5 a.m.
*Central Bank weekly survey of economists at 8:30 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*Cemig (CMIG4 BZ) may name Vale’s Agnelli as CEO, Folha Reports
*Banco do Brasil (BBAS3 BS) may issue bonds to fund project for
Olympics  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 1 percent to 69,268.29
*The real rose 1.5 percent to 1.6070 per dollar  To contact the reporter on this story:
